# Implementation Plan - Storefront Pages

Add storefront functionality to Planetravel including product display, ordering, and customer registration using GraphQL.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> I am assuming the GraphQL schema structure for `Product`, `Order`, and `Customer` as introspection was truncated. I will verify these fields during implementation.
> - **Product**: `id`, `name`, `description`, `price`, `imageUrl`
> - **Customer**: `id`, `name`, `email`, `password`
> - **Order**: `id`, `productId`, `customerId`, `quantity`

## Proposed Changes

### Dependencies
- [NEW] Install `@apollo/client` and `graphql`

### Infrastructure
#### [NEW] [apolloClient.ts](file:///d:/code/mern/planetravel/src/apolloClient.ts)
- Initialize Apollo Client pointing to `http://localhost:8000/graphql`

#### [MODIFY] [main.tsx](file:///d:/code/mern/planetravel/src/main.tsx)
- Wrap [App](file:///d:/code/mern/planetravel/src/App.tsx#13-32) with `ApolloProvider`

### Storefront Features
Create new feature directory `src/features/storefront`

#### [NEW] [ProductListPage.tsx](file:///d:/code/mern/planetravel/src/features/storefront/ProductListPage.tsx)
- Query `products`
- Display grid of products using DaisyUI Cards
- "Buy" button triggers order flow

#### [NEW] [RegistrationPage.tsx](file:///d:/code/mern/planetravel/src/features/storefront/RegistrationPage.tsx)
- Mutation `registerCustomer` (or similar)
- Form with Name, Email, Password

#### [NEW] [OrderModal.tsx](file:///d:/code/mern/planetravel/src/features/storefront/OrderModal.tsx)
- Mutation `createOrder`
- Simple form to confirm quantity and place order

#### [MODIFY] [App.tsx](file:///d:/code/mern/planetravel/src/App.tsx)
- Add routes:
    - `/products` -> `ProductListPage`
    - `/register` -> `RegistrationPage`

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `npm run testv` to ensure no regressions.
- I will add basic component tests if time permits.

### Manual Verification
1.  **Registration**: Go to `/register`, sign up a new user. Verify success message.
2.  **Products**: Go to `/products`, see list of products.
3.  **Order**: Click "Buy" on a product, place order. Verify order success.
